well-funded and well sort

02:50:37.050 --> 02:50:39.470
of oiled to move very fast.

02:50:39.470 --> 02:50:41.410
So coming-- sorry.

02:50:41.410 --> 02:50:49.190
So coming out of the Ebola crisis
because education is my background

02:50:49.190 --> 02:50:52.550
so I could speak to you about
what we did to reopen schools.

02:50:52.550 --> 02:50:56.380
One of the major concerns
was the safety of children.

02:50:56.380 --> 02:51:00.200
Given the infrastructure and the
fact that children share everything

02:51:00.200 --> 02:51:03.670
in the classroom including seats
and you have four to five seating

02:51:03.670 --> 02:51:08.670
to a seat and Ebola is transmitted
by touch, all you needed was

02:51:08.670 --> 02:51:12.450
for one kid to transmit it to
potentially an entire classroom.

02:51:12.450 --> 02:51:15.050
So, there were working
groups established

02:51:15.050 --> 02:51:16.860
that focused on everything.

02:51:16.860 --> 02:51:19.270
There were protocols
that were developed

02:51:19.270 --> 02:51:22.120 position:56%
and received certification from WHO.

02:51:22.120 --> 02:51:26.940
And then we implemented a system
of distributing wash buckets.

02:51:26.940 --> 02:51:30.350
I don't know if I have-- somewhere
in here I have the photo of it.

02:51:30.350 --> 02:51:33.720
It's basically a plastic
bucket with a little spigot

02:51:33.720 --> 02:51:36.280
at the bottom that's
fused into another bucket

02:51:36.280 --> 02:51:39.230
and you put a little
bleach and soap in it.

02:51:39.230 --> 02:51:42.690
And every child have to wash
their hands coming into school.

02:51:42.690 --> 02:51:46.400
We also procured tons
and tons of thermometers.

02:51:46.400 --> 02:51:50.350
Every school received at least two
thermometers for 50 kid and then

02:51:50.350 --> 02:51:54.190
